God grant me strength.

1667
02:17:37.920 --> 02:17:39.710
(SHOUTING IN GERMAN)

1668
02:17:44.170 --> 02:17:45.720
Displace!

1669
02:17:45.800 --> 02:17:47.220
Come on!

1670
02:17:50.970 --> 02:17:52.390
(SCREAMING)

1671
02:18:03.030 --> 02:18:05.780
MILLER: Cover, Upham! Cover! Cover!

1672
02:18:22.550 --> 02:18:24.510
MELLISH: I'm out of 30-caliber.

1673
02:18:27.930 --> 02:18:30.760
Blessed be the Lord, my strength,
which teaches my hands to war

1674
02:18:30.850 --> 02:18:33.220
and my fingers to fight.

1675
02:18:41.730 --> 02:18:44.230
My goodness and my fortress,

1676
02:18:44.320 --> 02:18:46.990
my high tower and my deliverer,

1677
02:18:49.570 --> 02:18:52.780
my shield and he in whom I trust.

1678
02:18:55.830 --> 02:18:57.910
Come here, baby.

1679
02:19:20.520 --> 02:19:22.310
Parker, get down!

1680
02:19:44.000 --> 02:19:46.420
Captain, that
20-millimeter's killing us.

1681
02:19:46.500 --> 02:19:48.800
We gotta try to flank it somehow.

1682
02:19:48.920 --> 02:19:51.760
Well, let me get over for the top shot.

1683
02:20:07.440 --> 02:20:09.530
(TANK RAPIDLY APPROACHING)

1684
02:20:16.280 --> 02:20:17.700
HENDERSON: Upham!

1685
02:20:26.420 --> 02:20:27.840
(EXPLOSIONS)

1686
02:20:36.550 --> 02:20:41.020
Upham! Upham!
Upham, ammo, God damn it!

1687
02:21:06.330 --> 02:21:08.130
(SOLDIERS SPEAKING GERMAN)

1688
02:21:24.230 --> 02:21:26.650
I'm jammed! I'm jammed!
You got any 30-cal?

1689
02:21:26.730 --> 02:21:28.400
- I'm out.
- Shit.

1690
02:21:29.270 --> 02:21:31.190
(BANGING)

1691
02:21:40.200 --> 02:21:42.700
Upham! Upham!

1692
02:21:49.540 --> 02:21:50.710
(THUD)

1693
02:22:22.700 --> 02:22:23.990
(GASPING)

1694
02:22:40.890 --> 02:22:42.350
Reiben!

1695
02:22:48.190 --> 02:22:49.600
(SHOUTING)

1696
02:23:08.830 --> 02:23:13.000
I'm out! I need another bandoleer!
Anybody got a bandoleer?

1697
02:23:35.820 --> 02:23:37.320
(YELLING)

1698
02:23:37.990 --> 02:23:40.200
God! God!

1699
02:23:44.490 --> 02:23:47.410
You stupid son of a bitch!

1700
02:23:53.080 --> 02:23:54.710
(YELLING)

1701
02:24:27.370 --> 02:24:29.120
(SPEAKING GERMAN)

1702
02:24:31.040 --> 02:24:33.620
Let's stop. Let's stop. Let's stop.
Listen to me! Listen to me! Stop!

1703
02:24:33.710 --> 02:24:35.460
Stop! Don't...

1704
02:24:39.210 --> 02:24:41.050
(SPEAKING GERMAN)

1705
02:24:43.470 --> 02:24:44.760
(CHOKING)

1706
02:24:46.720 --> 02:24:48.060
(SHUSHING)

1707
02:25:02.740 --> 02:25:04.410
(SHOUTING IN GERMAN)

1708
02:25:12.500 --> 02:25:17.330
Son of a bitch!
Son of a bitch! Son of a bitch!

1709
02:25:17.420 --> 02:25:19.210
Son of a bitch!

1710
02:25:20.670 --> 02:25:21.710
Bitch!

1711
02:26:10.300 --> 02:26:11.680
(SOBBING)

1712
02:26:21.520 --> 02:26:23.320
(SOLDIERS SHOUTING IN GERMAN)

1713
02:26:40.750 --> 02:26:43.840
- I'm out.
- Those 60 rounds.

1714
02:26:45.260 --> 02:26:48.430
- We can use them without the tube.
- How?

1715
02:26:48.510 --> 02:26:51.470
Fuse-arming wire, set back, heave it!

1716
02:27:07.190 --> 02:27:08.860
Panzerschreck!

1717
02:27:42.900 --> 02:27:45.150
We're going to the Alamo.

1718
02:27:55.410 --> 02:27:57.240
Alamo! Alamo!

1719
02:28:00.830 --> 02:28:02.620
(SHOUTING IN GERMAN)

1720
02:28:16.760 --> 02:28:19.100
We'll take it! You fall back!

1721
02:28:19.180 --> 02:28:22.770
- You be right behind us!
- Soon as we're in business!

1722
02:28:26.770 --> 02:28:28.860
Displace. Reiben.

1723
02:28:31.360 --> 02:28:32.780
Reload.

1724
02:28:34.280 --> 02:28:36.120
(SOLDIERS SHOUTING IN GERMAN)

1725
02:29:21.620 --> 02:29:23.160
All right, go.

1726
02:29:24.410 --> 02:29:25.500
We're blowing the bridge!

1727
02:29:25.580 --> 02:29:28.500
- Get off! Clear the bridge!
- Displace...

1728
02:29:31.210 --> 02:29:32.670
(HORVATH EXCLAIMS)

1729
02:29:51.360 --> 02:29:54.360
MILLER: Sarge! Mike, are you all right?

1730
02:29:54.440 --> 02:29:57.000
- I just got the wind knocked out of me.
- Well, get out of here!

1731
02:29:57.030 --> 02:30:00.450
Take cover!
We're going to blow this bridge!

1732
02:30:01.870 --> 02:30:03.660
Come on, come on!

1733
02:30:08.460 --> 02:30:11.300
Tiger coming!
Coming across the bridge!

1734
02:30:12.460 --> 02:30:14.260
(SPEAKING GERMAN)

1735
02:30:43.370 --> 02:30:46.660
(FAINTLY) Captain,
get behind something!

1736
02:30:46.750 --> 02:30:49.420
(FAINTLY) Come on, Captain, move it!

1737
02:31:12.360 --> 02:31:13.570
Mike.

1738
02:31:18.780 --> 02:31:20.110
Mike!

1739
02:31:36.760 --> 02:31:38.510
(BULLET BUZZING)

1740
02:31:59.110 --> 02:32:00.360
REIBEN: Captain.

1741
02:32:03.160 --> 02:32:07.290
Captain, where the hell are you going?
Captain, get back here!

1742
02:33:46.760 --> 02:33:48.600
(ORDERING IN GERMAN)

1743
02:34:00.320 --> 02:34:01.650
Upham.

1744
02:34:32.640 --> 02:34:34.850
Hang in there, Captain.

1745
02:35:18.980 --> 02:35:20.690
REIBEN: Medic!

1746
02:35:23.480 --> 02:35:26.030
Medic! We got a medic?

1747
02:35:32.820 --> 02:35:35.700
They're tank-busters, sir. P-51s.

1748
02:35:36.660 --> 02:35:38.870
Angels on our shoulders.

1749
02:35:44.840 --> 02:35:46.550
What, sir?

1750
02:35:51.010 --> 02:35:52.390
James...

1751
02:35:54.180 --> 02:35:55.680
Earn this.

1752
02:35:59.940 --> 02:36:01.390
Earn it.

1753
02:36:30.840 --> 02:36:33.010
<i>MARSHALL: "My dear Mrs. Ryan,"</i>

1754
02:36:34.260 --> 02:36:36.720
<i>"it's with the most
profound sense of joy"</i>

1755
02:36:36.810 --> 02:36:41.980
<i>"that I write to inform you
your son Private James Ryan"</i>

1756
02:36:42.100 --> 02:36:44.190
<i>"is well and, at this very moment,"</i>

1757
02:36:44.270 --> 02:36:47.730
<i>"on his way home
from European battlefields."</i>

1758
02:36:47.820 --> 02:36:51.320
<i>"Reports from the front indicate
James did his duty in combat"</i>

1759
02:36:51.440 --> 02:36:54.950
<i>"with great courage
and steadfast dedication,"</i>

1760
02:36:55.530 --> 02:36:58.120
<i>"even after he was informed
of the tragic loss"</i>

1761
02:36:58.200 --> 02:37:01.790
<i>"your family has suffered
in this great campaign"</i>

1762
02:37:01.870 --> 02:37:05.290
<i>"to rid the world
of tyranny and oppression."</i>

1763
02:37:05.380 --> 02:37:08.630
<i>"I take great pleasure in joining
the Secretary of War,"</i>

1764
02:37:08.800 --> 02:37:10.880
<i>"the men and women
of the United States Army"</i>

1765
02:37:10.960 --> 02:37:13.340
<i>"and the citizens of a grateful nation"</i>

1766
02:37:13.470 --> 02:37:16.340
<i>"in wishing you good health
and many years of happiness"</i>

1767
02:37:16.470 --> 02:37:18.970
<i>"with James at your side."</i>

1768
02:37:20.140 --> 02:37:24.140
<i>"Nothing, not even the safe
return of a beloved son,"</i>

1769
02:37:24.230 --> 02:37:25.770
<i>"can compensate you"</i>

1770
02:37:25.850 --> 02:37:28.900
<i>"or the thousands
of other American families"</i>

1771
02:37:28.980 --> 02:37:32.360
<i>"who have suffered great loss
in this tragic war."</i>

1772
02:37:32.490 --> 02:37:35.950
<i>"And I might share with you some words
which have sustained me"</i>

1773
02:37:36.030 --> 02:37:40.160
<i>"through long, dark nights of peril,
loss and heartache."</i>

1774
02:37:40.240 --> 02:37:41.700
<i>"And I quote,"</i>

1775
02:37:43.040 --> 02:37:44.620
<i>"'I pray that our heavenly father"</i>

1776
02:37:44.710 --> 02:37:47.920
<i>"'may assuage the anguish
of your bereavement"</i>

1777
02:37:48.000 --> 02:37:49.960
<i>"'and leave you only
the cherished memory"</i>

1778
02:37:50.050 --> 02:37:52.050
<i>"'of the loved and lost"</i>

1779
02:37:52.170 --> 02:37:54.510
<i>"'and the solemn pride
that must be yours"</i>

1780
02:37:54.590 --> 02:37:59.350
<i>"'to have laid so costly a sacrifice
upon the altar of freedom."</i>

1781
02:38:00.100 --> 02:38:01.770
<i>"'Abraham Lincoln.' "</i>

1782
02:38:02.350 --> 02:38:04.770
<i>"Yours very sincerely and respectfully,"</i>

1783
02:38:04.850 --> 02:38:08.190
<i>"George C Marshall,
General, Chief of Staff."</i>

1784
02:38:59.570 --> 02:39:01.910
My family is with me today.

1785
02:39:02.870 --> 02:39:05.700
They wanted to come with me.

1786
02:39:07.370 --> 02:39:08.500
To be honest with you,

1787
02:39:08.580 --> 02:39:11.880
I wasn't sure how I'd feel
coming back here.

1788
02:39:15.260 --> 02:39:18.680
Every day I think about
what you said to me

1789
02:39:18.760 --> 02:39:20.890
that day on the bridge.

1790
02:39:22.760 --> 02:39:26.220
And I've tried to live my life
the best I could.

1791
02:39:27.310 --> 02:39:29.730
I hope that was enough.

1792
02:39:30.480 --> 02:39:33.230
I hope that, at least in your eyes,

1793
02:39:35.070 --> 02:39:38.780
I've earned what all of you
have done for me.

1794
02:39:52.290 --> 02:39:53.630
James.

1795
02:39:55.920 --> 02:39:57.920
"Captain John H Miller."

1796
02:40:06.600 --> 02:40:10.480
- Tell me I've led a good life.
- What?

1797
02:40:11.770 --> 02:40:13.980
Tell me I'm a good man.

1798
02:40:21.200 --> 02:40:22.820
You are.

